Zhelev and endangered relations with its neighbours, Agencies report from
Sofia.
Mr Zhirinovsky, who arrived on Saturday, had described his Bulgarian friend
and adviser, Mr Svetoslav Stoilov, as the country's next president. He also
accused Bulgaria's neighbours, Greece and Turkey, of planning to conquer the
Balkans and described Romania as an 'artificial state'.
