<HEADLINE>
FT  24 DEC 93 / International Company News: Amdahl expects deeper losses in
fourth quarter
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MARTIN DICKSON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Amdahl, the Californian mainframe computer manufacturer, expects to report a
fourth-quarter loss of more than 35 cents a share - greater than Wall
Street's expectations, writes Martin Dickson.
The company, which has been suffering from a downturn in the mainframe
market and does not have other products to fall back on, said unit volumes
had increased in the fourth quarter over the low level of the third quarter.
However, margins had declined because of pressure on pricing and a shift in
sales mix towards smaller, dual processor systems.
