<HEADLINE>
FT  24 DEC 93 / Finance and the Family: Your CGT allowances
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The table shows capital gains tax indexation allowances for assets sold in
November. Multiply the original cost of the asset by the figure for the
month in which you bought it. Subtract the result from the proceeds of your
sale, and the balance will be your taxable gain or loss*. Suppose that you
bought shares for Pounds 6,000 in September 1985 and sold them in November
1993 for Pounds 13,000. Multiplying the original cost by the September 1985
figure of 1.484 gives a total of Pounds 8,904. Subtracting that from Pounds
13,000 gives a capital gain of Pounds 4,096, which is within the 1993-94 CGT
allowance of Pounds 5,800. If selling shares bought before April 6 1982, you
should use the March 1982 figure. The RPI in November was 141.6.
*For shares sold on or after November 30, it is no longer possible to use
indexation to create, or to increase, a loss.
