<HEADLINE>
FT  24 DEC 93 / Briefcase, Q&amp;A: No relief on share loss
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
I quite understand that, from last month's Budget, losses can no longer be
indexed; but can you please advise on the following. Ward Group plc shares
were declared 'of negligible value' in July 1992 and I have not yet
established this loss. It is my intention to set it against gains in the
present year, 1993-94. Will I be able to index this loss to July 1992, or
even to October 1993 (the month before the new legislation became
effective)?
No, you will get no indexation relief at all. Had you submitted a negligible
value claim before Budget day, you could have got indexation relief up to
the month in which the claim was submitted; but we take it that when you
say: 'I have not yet established this loss,' you mean: 'I have not yet
submitted a negligible-value claim under section 24(2) of the Taxation of
Chargeable Gains Act 1992'.
Write to the Inland Revenue Public Enquiry Room, Somerset House, Strand,
London, WC2R 1LB, for a free copy of the Budget day press release IR28
(Capital gains: indexation allowance and capital losses).
No legal responsibility can be accepted by the Financial Times for the
answers given in these columns. All enquiries will be answered by post as
soon as possible.
</TEXT>
