Sir, The leased territories in Hong Kong must be returned to the landlord,
the People's Republic of China. If Britain feels morally responsible for the
sub-tenants, the people of Hong Kong, then it should provide another place
of abode for those of them who do not wish to live directly under the rules
laid down by the landlord.
Any other action is an admission of flawed moral perceptions.
