<DATELINE>
   STUTTGART
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
IBM Deutschland Inform-ationssysteme, German unit of International Business
Machines of the US, said it would extend working hours for its employees
next year without paying them more, Reuter reports from Stuttgart.
IBM Deutschland said many of its 12,000 workers would work 38 hours a week
from January, instead of 36 hours, without extra pay.
IBM, which had sought a 40 hour working week, said it had reached an accord
with the DAG white collar union.
