<HEADLINE>
FT  23 DEC 93 / International Company News: HK railways in Dollars 1bn debt
programme
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LOUISE LUCAS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   HONG KONG
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Hong Kong's Mass Transit Railway Corporation (MTRC) has arranged a USDollars
1bn debt issuance programme, less than a week after having its credit rating
cut.
Last Friday, Moody's cut the MTRC's rating for Hong Kong dollar-denominated
debt to A1 from Aa2. The move comes with concerns for political stability in
China and the possible impact on the colony. Moody's saw vulnerability in
the Hong Kong/US dollar peg.
Debt issued under the new programme, signed yesterday, can be denominated in
any currency, subject to agreement with MTRC, with a maturity of between one
month and 30 years. It may take the form of fixed, zero-coupon or
floating-rate notes.
The programme replaces a HKDollars 3bn medium-term note programme set up in
1988 and which has now matured.
