<HEADLINE>
FT  23 DEC 93 / UK Company News: KPMG sued over Medway valuation
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Two former directors of Medway Ports are suing accountants KPMG Peat Marwick
for alleged negligence in a share valuation, which they claim deprived them
of a multi-million pound windfall.
The suit was launched by former operations director Mr Des Crampton and
ex-legal director Mr Keith Middleton, who were made redundant along with
hundreds of employees earlier this year.
They are disputing the 250p valuation by KPMG in March, just months before
the company agreed to a takeover bid by Mersey Docks at Pounds 37.25 a
share. Employees who were made redundant were required to surrender their
shares, some to directors of the company, at Pounds 2.50. Mr Crampton and Mr
Middleton claim to have lost more than Pounds 4m by the KPMG valuation.
The company's four directors received shares and cash worth Pounds 20m in
the takeover.
A valuation by accountants Ernst &amp; Young found the shares would have been
worth more than Pounds 2.50. KPMG has claimed the value was depressed, in
part by uncertainty over staffing levels.
Mr Crampton said he expected other former shareholders to take similar
action.
</TEXT>
