FT  23 DEC 93 / UK Company News: BAA chief makes Pounds 0.63m on sale of
share options
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TIM BURT
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir John Egan, chief executive of BAA, yesterday made Pounds 628,000 on the
exercise of share options in the airports operator.
The company told the Stock Exchange that Sir John, whose remuneration last
year totalled Pounds 768,000, had bought 261,500 ordinary shares at 384p
each under the BAA senior employee share option scheme.
After exercising his option, he subsequently sold 99,368 shares at Pounds
10.16 per share.
The former chairman of Jaguar, who took over at BAA in 1991, still retains
167,946 ordinary shares in the company. Sir John also disclosed that he had
a further 84,290 shares under option.
Shares in the company - which operates Heathrow, Gatwick and Stansted
airports - rose 11p to close at Pounds 10.24.
